reviews.review_text: A decent recording of an okay show Hardly a standout performance but not really all that bad either. The first set is pretty good overall while the second set has it's moments. There is a soundboard source for set 2 but the first couple of songs on that source have problems, unfortunately. It's a shame that the first set doesn't circulate as a board but this isn't a bad audience considering the venue.

Vince Welnick Vince sang on Baba O'Riley and Tomorrow Never Knows... I think these two songs showcase his ability to add to the group. I thought this was a great show, though seeing the video on Youtube, it doesn't look like the band was having fun for a lot of it...
